HEADWORD: Synclinorium
<hw>Syn`cli*no"ri*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Synclinoria</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <?/ to lay together + <?/ mountain.]</ety> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>
<def>A mountain range owing its origin to the progress of a
geosynclinal, and ending in a catastrophe of displacement and
upturning.</def> <rj><au>Dana.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
